               <msContents>
                  <summary>Abunä Täklä Mika'el and Wälätä
                            Kidan Codex <p>Fol. 1v: Illegible notes in pencil in another hand, including
                                "My father, please bless my learning." </p>
                     <p> Fols. 2r, 10r, 32v,
                                33r-38v, 40v: The owner's name Abunä Täklä Mika'el and his wife's
                                name Wälätä Kidan appear in the text. </p>
                     <p> No scribe
                                listed.</p>
                     <p> No miniatures.</p>
                     <p>Fol. 41v: The translator of the
                                text is named: "I, Gäbrä Kərəstos, translated this book from the
                                language of the Afəngi [sic, Afärəngi] to the language of
                                Ethiopia."</p>
                     
                     <p>References: Regarding Prayer of
                                Mary at Golgotha, see Sylvain Grébaut, "La prière de Marie au
                                Golgotha," JA, vol. 226 (1935), pp. 273-86; and Basset, René. Les
                                Apocryphes éthiopiens traduit en français I–XI. Paris: Bibliotheque
                                de la Haute Science, 1803–1909, V, pp. 30-47; Strelcyn, Stefan.
                                Catalogue des manuscrits éthiopiens de l'Accademia Nazionale dei
                                Lincei: Fonds Conti Rossini et Fonds Caetani 209, 375, 376, 377,
                                378. Rome: Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei, 1976. no. 47, fol. 73r.
                                Regarding Sword of the Divinity, Sylvain Grébaut, "La prière Sayfa
                                malakot," Aethiopica 4 (1936) 1–6. (Abbadie) 171, fol. 29v, Conti
                                Rossini, Notice, no. 104; Abbadie 186, fol. 104, Conti Rossini,
                                Notice, no. 233; Strelcyn, Lincei, 47, fol. 88v. Regarding Prayer to
                                Jesus ("Guard me"), Sylvain Grébaut, "La priére 'Eqabani' ou les
                                litanies du Christ" Orientalia nuova ser.,4,1935, 427-3; Chaîne,
                                "Répertoire," no. 371; Encyclopedia Aethiopica, vol. 2, p. 345.
                                Regarding "Prayer to the God of the Luminaries," Säbattu Kidanat.
                                Qəddase Maryam Mälkə'a Guba'e. Täsfa Press, Addis Ababa 1959 EC, pp.
                                38ff; Mäsəhafä Qəddase. Bä-Gə'əzənna bä-Amarəñña, Täsfa Press, Addis
                                Ababa 1951 EC, pp. 199-200; Marcos Daoud, and H. E. Blatta Marsie
                                Hazen, The Liturgy of the Ethiopian Church. Cairo: Egyptian Book
                                Press, 1959. pp. 244-245; Sebastian Euringer, "Die Ethiopische
                                Anaphora des hl. Epiphanius Bischofs der Insel Cypern," Oriens
                                Christianus, third ser., vol. I (1926), pp. 126-128; Encyclopedia
                                Aethiopica, vol. 2, p. 249.</p>
                  </summary>
